for Strings variables:

 <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
            var subjectOne = " JavaScript, ";
            var subjectTwo = " HTML, ";
            var subjectThree = " CSS";
            var subjects = subjectOne + subjectTwo + subjectThree;
            document.write("The subjects: " + subjects);
        </script>

for Numbers variables:

 <p id="total"></p>
        <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
            var firstNum = 34.50;
            var secondNum = 120;
            var total = firstNum + secondNum;
            document.getElementById("total").innerHTML = total;
        </script>

 <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
            var firstNum = 34.50;
            var secondNum = 120;
            var total = firstNum + secondNum;
            document.write("The total: " + total);
        </script>

Replace in the Web page below:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <html lang="en">
    <head>
        <title>JavaScript Variables Application</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h3>JavaScript Variables Application</h3>
        <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
            var firstNum = 34.50;
            var secondNum = 120;
            var total = firstNum + secondNum;
            document.write("The total: " + total);
        </script>
    </body>
    </html>
